description: From Latin natēs, plural of natis.

entries.meaning: (anatomy, medicine) The two anterior of the four lobes on the dorsal side of the midbrain of most mammals; the anterior optic lobes.

examples: Enderby watched her warily as she lay prone, having kicked the clothes off the bed, her nates silvered by the Roman moonlight to the likeness of a meringue.

entries.meaning: (zoology) The umbones of a bivalve shell.
